            <sparkle:version>24</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.25</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>13.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <pubDate>Sat, 01 Mar 2026 23:30:00 -0600</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <h2>C200 Controller v1.0.25</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Tally is now much more robust on rough WiFi — a 5-second ping detects dead WebSocket connections and reconnects automatically (root cause of the camera 1 stuck tally)</li>
                    <li>Rapid TSL cuts no longer pile up stale commands — each new tally cancels any in-flight command from the previous cut</li>
                    <li>Smarter reconnect logic — deliberate socket resets no longer trigger a second reconnect attempt</li>
                    <li>TSL stream parsing is more resilient — fragmented TCP packets no longer cause buffered data to be dropped</li>
                </ul>
            ]]></description>
